\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl360\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The wooden creak and clacking of horse hoofs filled the journey after Eddie, Torrie, Markus and Catherine boarded the carriage that agreed to take them to Gunther\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Farm, that is the northernmost point the carriage is willing to take them.}
\par\plain {Scents of hay and the faint earthy breeze drifting through the open sides of the carriage. Eddie sat quietly, his gaze fixed on the passing fields, The rifle sat leaning on his shoulder. Catherine, ever the scholar, kept stealing glances at the weapon. Finally, her curiosity got the better of her. }
\par\plain {Catherine then reaches her hand to touch one of the engravings.}
\par\plain {But as usual, Eddie swatter her hands away.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on, Edward.\u8221\'94 Catherine sighed, \u8220\'93Can\u8217\'92t I get just a little touch of it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, Catherine.\u8221\'94 Eddie reminded, \u8220\'93Dad said so.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Humph,\u8221\'94 Catherine said in mock pout, \u8220\'93Have it your way then.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Markus and Torrie laughed at the exchange, but Catherine is far from over, she continued,}
\par\plain {"But I've been meaning to ask about that flintlock of yours. It's not exactly what you see every day, especially for someone helping out at the apothecary." }
\par\plain {"It's more of a hand-me-down, I guess," he sighed, "Back when Weshaven was still full of Streamwyrms, Dad taught my brother Alfred how to use it. Alfred would go into the shore with the others and scare off anything too close to the Apothecary. Sometimes, he'd even shoot them if they were too bold." }
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Streamwyrms? What\u8217\'92s that?\u8221\'94 Torrie asked,}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s those fishes coming out of the shores every August, remember? Sharp teeth, four legs, you were almost bitten by one last summer.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh those!\u8221\'94 Torrie said, \u8220\'93But they are so cute, why did Alfred shoot them?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93No they aren\u8217\'92t cute, Torrie, they\u8217\'92re pest!\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\i0 Eddie hissed}
\par\plain {Catherine tilted her head, her gaze flicking back to the rifle. "And now? I assume there aren't any Streamwyrms around anymore." }
\par\plain {"Not really," Eddie replied. "They still comes out of the shores every August, since Alfred\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s not around, I takes his place, but honestly Markus was much more better shot than me, so I haven't had to use this thing in ages. Honestly, it's just been collecting dust." }
\par\plain {"So why bring it now?" Catherine pressed, a note of curiosity creeping into her tone. }
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Eh,\u8221\'94 Eddie shrugged. "Because it's cool." }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93You just said that Robert asked you to take it.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\i0 Catherine said}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But it\u8217\'92s still cool nonetheless.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Since it\u8217\'92s oh so cool,\u8221\'94 Catherine said theatrically, \u8220\'93You would let me touch them.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93No!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\i0
